    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flat, folding cases for holding banknotes and papers, and typically of a size designed to fit the inside pocket of a man's jacket of the 19th and early 20th centuries.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
